-----------------------------------------------------
TO BEGIN EXECUTION
-----------------------------------------------------
-To start the execution, run the Convergecast.java file.

-----------------------------------------------------
FLOW OF EXECUTION
-----------------------------------------------------
-The Convergecast constructor calls the init() method which is used to initialize the tree.
-Post that, we call maxElem(tree.root) to get the maximum value of the node in the tree rooted at 'root'
-Then we call the printChildren() to print all the children of root that are directly accessible from the 
root. Here, we have used the post-order tree traversal.